---
import LegalPageLayout from "../layouts/LegalPageLayout.astro";
---

<LegalPageLayout
  title="Delete your data (without deleting account) - CheqSplit"
  description="Remove CheqSplit app data without closing your account. Google Play “delete data” information."
  canonicalPath="/delete-data/"
>
  <article class="legal-doc text-slate-800" aria-labelledby="del-data-title">
    <header class="mb-10 border-b border-slate-200 pb-8">
      <h1 id="del-data-title" class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 md:text-4xl">
        Delete your data (without deleting account)
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> April 16, 2026
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-10 text-base leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <strong>CheqSplit</strong> (this app on Google Play) lets you remove some or all of your app data{" "}
        <strong>without</strong> closing your account. This page is the link required by Google Play for “delete data” requests.
      </p>

      <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="step1">
        <h2 id="step1" class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Step 1 — In the app (fastest)</h2>
        <p>You can delete content yourself:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Trips, bills, and drafts:</strong> Remove or archive items from the app as supported by each screen (e.g. delete a trip,
            clear a bill, discard a draft).
          </li>
          <li><strong>Local-only data:</strong> Clearing app storage or uninstalling removes data stored only on your device.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Changes you make in the app sync to our servers where your account uses cloud features; removing content in-app removes that content from your active workspace where technically possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="step2">
        <h2 id="step2" class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Step 2 — Email us for server-side cleanup</h2>
        <p>If you need specific data removed from our systems (e.g. copies you cannot delete in the app, or a mistake), contact us:</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal space-y-3 pl-6">
          <li>
            Email{" "}
            <a class="font-medium text-brand-600 underline hover:text-brand-700" href="mailto:lungusterus@gmail.com"
              >lungusterus@gmail.com</a
            >
            {" "}from the address linked to your account (or describe how we can verify you).
          </li>
          <li>Subject: <strong>Data deletion request (no account closure)</strong>.</li>
          <li>List what to delete (e.g. “all trips before 2025”, “trip named X”, “receipt images from date …”).</li>
        </ol>
        <p>We may ask you to confirm identity before changing or deleting data tied to your account.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="del-vs-keep">
        <h2 id="del-vs-keep" class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">What we delete vs keep</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-3 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Deleted on request / in-app:</strong> User-created trips, bills, line items, participant labels, and similar app content you remove or that we remove after a verified email request,
            subject to backups and legal holds below.
          </li>
          <li><strong>May be kept temporarily:</strong> Encrypted backups or replicas until they expire in normal backup cycles (typically short-term).</li>
          <li><strong>May be kept longer if required by law:</strong> Minimal records for tax, fraud prevention, or legal process.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Other users’ copies:</strong> If you shared a bill, other participants may still have their copy; we cannot delete data on someone else’s device.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Subscriptions:</strong> Purchase history with Apple / Google follows store policies; deleting app data does not erase store receipts.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="timing2">
        <h2 id="timing2" class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Timing</h2>
        <p>
          We aim to complete verified <strong>partial</strong> deletion requests within <strong>30 days</strong>, unless law or safety requires otherwise.
        </p>
      </section>

      <nav class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-8 text-sm text-slate-600" aria-label="Related legal pages">
        <p>
          To delete your <strong>entire account</strong> instead, see{" "}
          <a class="font-medium text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700" href="/delete-account/">Delete your account</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          General privacy:{" "}
          <a class="font-medium text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700" href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </article>
</LegalPageLayout>
